Duplicate payment prevention requires idempotency, database constraints, and duplicate detection:

**1. Idempotency Key Approach (Best Practice)**:
```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/payments")
public class PaymentController {

    @PostMapping
    public ResponseEntity<PaymentResponse> createPayment(
            @RequestHeader("Idempotency-Key") String idempotencyKey,
            @RequestBody PaymentRequest request) {

        return paymentService.processPaymentIdempotent(idempotencyKey, request);
    }
}

@Service
public class PaymentService {

    @Transactional
    public ResponseEntity<PaymentResponse> processPaymentIdempotent(
            String idempotencyKey, PaymentRequest request) {

        // Step 1: Check if this idempotency key was already processed
        Optional<Payment> existingPayment =
            paymentRepository.findByIdempotencyKey(idempotencyKey);

        if (existingPayment.isPresent()) {
            // Duplicate request detected
            Payment payment = existingPayment.get();

            return ResponseEntity.ok(PaymentResponse.builder()
                .transactionId(payment.getId())
                .status(payment.getStatus())
                .isDuplicate(true)
                .originalTransactionId(payment.getId())
                .message("This payment was already processed at: " +
                        payment.getCreatedAt())
                .build());
        }

        // Step 2: Process new payment
        try {
            Payment payment = new Payment();
            payment.setIdempotencyKey(idempotencyKey);
            payment.setAmount(request.getAmount());
            payment.setStatus(PaymentStatus.PROCESSING);
            Payment savedPayment = paymentRepository.save(payment);

            // Step 3: Call payment gateway
            String transactionId = paymentGateway.charge(
                request.getCardToken(),
                request.getAmount()
            );

            // Step 4: Update payment status
            savedPayment.setStatus(PaymentStatus.SUCCESS);
            savedPayment.setTransactionId(transactionId);
            paymentRepository.save(savedPayment);

            return ResponseEntity.ok(PaymentResponse.builder()
                .transactionId(transactionId)
                .status(PaymentStatus.SUCCESS)
                .isDuplicate(false)
                .message("Payment processed successfully")
                .build());

        } catch (PaymentGatewayException e) {
            return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.PAYMENT_REQUIRED)
                .body(PaymentResponse.builder()
                    .status(PaymentStatus.FAILED)
                    .isDuplicate(false)
                    .errorMessage(e.getMessage())
                    .build());
        }
    }
}
```

