**JWT vs OAuth Comparison**:
```
Aspect              | JWT                  | OAuth 2.0
--------------------|----------------------|----------------------
Purpose             | Authentication       | Authorization
Token format        | Self-contained       | Any format (opaque)
Signature           | Cryptographically    | Server validates
User info           | Inside token         | Separate lookup
Revocation          | Difficult            | Immediate
Third-party access  | No                   | Yes
Complexity          | Simple               | Complex
```

**Combined Use Case: JWT with OAuth**:
```
OAuth 2.0: User authenticates via Google/Facebook
        ↓
Server generates JWT token
        ↓
JWT used for subsequent API requests
        ↓
No need to call OAuth provider each request
```

**Key Differences**:
- **JWT**: Stateless token containing user info
- **OAuth**: Authorization framework for delegated access
- **Together**: OAuth for login, JWT for API access
